<subSubSection id="C33311E1FFE37F0A99F7E05DD452FAA5" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B96426AFFE37F0A99F7E05DD556FCC9" blockId="38.[151,1437,732,1295]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE37F0A99F7E05DD530FC96" bold="true" box="[198,546,802,828]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
Andes in 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE37F0A9BA2E05DD414FC96" box="[659,774,802,828]" name="Colombia" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE37F0A9A71E05DD4AEFC96" box="[832,956,802,828]" name="Venezuela" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
. It forms dense colonies in open habitats in montane forests, at 
<quantity id="4CD1EF8FFFE37F0A98ABE036D52DFCC9" box="[410,575,841,867]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="m" value="2150.0" valueMax="2700.0" valueMin="1600.0">1600–2700 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96426AFFE37F0A99F7E010D452FAA5" blockId="38.[151,1437,732,1295]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE37F0A99F7E010D621FC23" bold="true" box="[198,307,879,905]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE37F0A9802E00FD6E0FC23" authorityName="Nakai" authorityYear="1950" baseAuthorityName="Moritz" box="[307,498,880,905]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE37F0A9802E00FD6E0FC23" box="[307,498,880,905]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Sticherus nudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to a group of four confusingly similar Mesoamerican and Andean species, including 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE37F0A984DE0E8D571FC1A" authorityName="Ostergaard &amp; Ollgaard" authorityYear="2001" box="[380,611,919,944]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevitomentosus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE37F0A984DE0E8D571FC1A" box="[380,611,919,944]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">S. brevitomentosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE37F0A9B45E0E8D5F1FC1A" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" box="[628,739,919,944]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ovatus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE37F0A9B45E0E8D5F1FC1A" box="[628,739,919,944]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">S. ovatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE37F0A9A18E0E8D4D9FC1A" authorityName="Copeland" authorityYear="1947" baseAuthorityName="Christ" box="[809,971,919,944]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pteridellus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE37F0A9A18E0E8D4D9FC1A" box="[809,971,919,944]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">S. pteridellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These all have ovate segments, nonpectinate proximal branches, approximate, usually flat segments, generally rather sparsely scaly branches, ovate-lanceolate to ovate scales that appear papyraceous and dull whitish to brown when dry, and finally, they also lack aphlebiae. Among these species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE37F0A9BB6E775D5FBFB89" authorityName="Nakai" authorityYear="1950" baseAuthorityName="Moritz" box="[647,745,1034,1059]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE37F0A9BB6E775D5FBFB89" box="[647,745,1034,1059]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">S. nudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by abaxially protruding ultimate branches, 1 
<superScript id="7C5CEF22FFE37F0A9997E74ED7A3FB95" attach="left" box="[166,177,1073,1087]" fontSize="6" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">st</superScript>
branches longer than the 2 
<superScript id="7C5CEF22FFE37F0A9B33E74ED501FB95" attach="left" box="[514,531,1073,1087]" fontSize="6" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">nd</superScript>
ones, arched branches, petioles and rachises much thicker than the pinna branches, thick rhizomes with scattered, rigid scales, cartilaginous, undulate segment margins, abaxially glabrous segments with raised, parallel veinlets, sparse, reduced, mixed ovate and linear scales restricted to the midveins and sometimes around the inframedial sori, and ovate to rounded branch and bud scales with usually glandular apices. The arched branches are reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE37F0A9A94E7B0D343FB42" authorityName="Ostergaard &amp; Ollgaard" authorityYear="2001" box="[933,1105,1231,1256]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aurantiacus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE37F0A9A94E7B0D343FB42" box="[933,1105,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">S. aurantiacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE37F0A9DBDE7B0D233FB42" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1990" box="[1164,1313,1231,1256]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tepuiensis">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE37F0A9DBDE7B0D233FB42" box="[1164,1313,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">S. tepuiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but these species are densely scaly, with narrowly lanceolate scales.
</paragraph>
